configure.ac: Do not call undeclared exit function

Implicit function declarations were removed from the C language in
1999, and future compilers are likely to treat them as errors by
default.

commit.message:
Improve portability of ticks per second calculations

Recent Linux versions define the start time from /proc/*/stat
as sysconf(_SC_CLK_TCK) instead of jiffies.

The Hurd docs also suggest using sysconf(_SC_CLK_TCK) instead of HZ.

See-also: https://www.gnu.org/software/hurd/hurd/porting/guidelines.html

commit.message:
p_start_time: return seconds instead of jiffies

The Linux kernel doesn't use jiffies any more.

Returning jiffies instead of seconds is a bit of a leaky abstraction.

commit.message:
Advertise keys for SIGTERM instead of SIGKILL in tree mode help

SIGKILL destroys processes without any chance of cleanup so
SIGTERM is usually preferable to prevent issues.

SIGKILL is still available for hung processes.

Add help and documentation for sending SIGINT, SIGHUP and SIGTERM

The relevant code was present, is now working but is undocumented.

Send signals when receiving the keys for SIGINT, SIGHUP and SIGTERM

These are mentioned in the code but do not work because
they are not passed to the signal dispatcher.

Add conversion for the key for SIGINT

This is documented to work but does not.

Check for HAVE_STRUCT_STAT_ST_RDEV before using struct stat st_rdev

Improves portability to some UNIXen.

Remove use of AC_TYPE_SIGNAL

It is an obsolete autoconf macro and it is unused by the code.

Suggested-by: autoupdate

Move AC_OUTPUT arguments to AC_CONFIG_FILES macro call

Passing args to the AC_OUTPUT autoconf macro is obsolete.

Changes-by: autoupdate

Replace AC_STRUCT_ST_RDEV with the appropriate AC_CHECK_MEMBERS call

The former is an obsolete autoconf macro.

Changes-by: autoupdate

Switch from AC_TRY_COMPILE to AC_COMPILE_IFELSE and AC_LANG_PROGRAM

The former autoconf macro is obsolete.

Changes-by: autoupdate

Use correct quoting in autoconf script

Results of some autoconf macros need quoting.

This will reduce the diffs when running autoupdate.

Suggested-by: autoupdate

Use reduced amount of space in autoconf script

This will reduce the diffs when running autoupdate.

Changes-by: autoupdate
